The paper discusses machine learning algorithms and their application to time series prediction, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. However, the focus on hyperparameter optimization and the use of Kernel Ridge regression make cs.LG (Machine Learning) the most likely category. The use of real traffic measurement data also suggests a potential fit with cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The use of optimization techniques and the focus on prediction accuracy suggest a potential fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
